Record Class IniConfig

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
com.google.common.labs.ini.IniConfig
@Immutable public record IniConfig(Map<String, List<IniConfig.Section>> sections) extends Record
A light-weight INI syntax parser, supporting key-values and sections.

The syntax looks like TOML (with sections, comments and key-value pairs). But no quoting or escaping, and whitespaces around keys and values are ignored. For example: 

 # optional global key values
 enabled = true
 active_time = 2025-10-30 15:30:00 America/Los_Angeles
 denied_statuses = DELETED, BLOCKED

 [user profile]  # line end comment
 name = John Doe
 home address = 123 Main St, Anytown, CA 98765

 [credentials]
 username = john # comment not included in value
 password = abcdef

A typical usage pattern: 


 var config = IniConfig.parse(input);

 boolean enabled = config.defaultSection().is("enabled");
 Instant activeTime = config.defaultSection().getInstant("start_time");
 List<Status> deniedStatuses =
     config.defaultSection().getEnumList("denied_statuses", Status.class);
 String userName = config.section("credentials").getString("username");

TOML list of tables is supported by using multiple sections of the same name (i.e. [plugin], not [[plugins]]), and you can access these sections using the sections(String) method.

Since:
9.4

      public List<IniConfig.Section> sections(String sectionName)
      Returns the potentially multiple sections identified by sectionName, case-sensitively. Useful for configuring what's known as "array of tables" in TOML, but instead of using the [[section]] syntax, you use the same [section] syntax.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if sectionName isn't found in the config
